The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 22 April is 272,265 (31,380.1 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 17 April, there were 2,583 new confirmed cases (297.7 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 10 April, there were 3,804 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 32% (1,221 fewer cases).
